title: Grateful Dead Live at Civic Arena on 1988-06-26
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Little Red Rooster, When Push Comes To Shove, Mama Tried-> Big River, Cumberland Blues, Gentlemen Start Your Engines, Big Railroad Blues, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Touch Of Gray, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band Reprise-> Drums-> Jam-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Hey Jude-> Black Peter-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text:
Nice Source Good, bright source, nice sound that catches the sparkle-tinkle of Jerry and Brent during this time.  Great to hear the crowd:  they get stoked in all the right places.  Not a lot of low-register Phil here, but you can hear his higher-end runs really well.

The show is pretty routine, as was pointed out in the reviews of the matrix source.  The Half-Step and Gentlemen are worth a listen, and it's always wise to hear every Playin' you can get your hands on...

The three stars are for the show, not the source.
